West Midlands Ambulance Service said the woman had been in cardiac arrest with head, chest and pelvic injuries after being hit at "high speed" and was taken to a hospital in Coventry.
Police officers were called to scene, near the A5121 Branston Interchange and Claymills Road, at about 20:30 BST and shut the road.
The northbound side of the A38 is now partially open.
Drivers are advised to avoid the area where possible due to delays on nearby routes.
Anyone with information about the incident is asked to contact police.
